# Game Harbour

Read `docs/PROJECT_PLAN.md` before large changes.

## Product

- Brand: **Game Harbour** (British English). Never use American "Harbor" or "GameHubber".
- **Master Bridge** (`/[locale]/bridge`) - auth required, professional host only: game library, create/edit games, run sessions
- **Player** (`/[locale]/play/[code]`) - mobile-first, no auth
- First system game: **El Dorado** (`docs/games/el-dorado.md`) - realistic Amazon treasure hunt, no supernatural
- **i18n**: `next-intl`, locales `ru` (default) and `en` (British English copy in `messages/en.json`); never hardcode user-facing strings

## Stack

- Next.js App Router + API routes
- PostgreSQL + Prisma - game templates, sessions, hosts
- S3-compatible storage (MinIO dev, R2 prod) for images
- Auth.js - hosts only; username + password (no email/SMTP)
- Realtime: Socket.io (`realtime/server.ts` locally, Render in prod); typed `RoomEvent`

## Code

- Follow `architecture.mdc`: SOLID, DRY, YAGNI, KISS; UI and business logic in separate files
- TypeScript strict, no `any`
- Tailwind mobile-first for `components/player/`
- User strings in `messages/{locale}.json` or DB i18n fields
- Dice/room logic in `src/session-engine/`; DB/auth in `src/server/`; never in components
- Uploads go through `lib/storage.ts`, never commit binary assets to git

## Scope

- Minimal diff; grounded realism in default game content
- Do not add frontend-only workarounds that skip DB when persistence is required
